{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":2408,"record_hash":"sha256:73425448c2464e5377910ca376148be608c1604875c5911712e1a5b4e9e2a512","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:07:36.039Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 0507b7\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1540\nOutput:\n---\nname: but-agentlog\nversion: 0.0.0\ndescription: \"Recover agent handoff context from GitButler agentlog captures. Use when finding related agent sessions for a branch, GitButler review / pull request / merge request, or change; inspecting session timelines; hydrating bounded records; or summarizing prior agent work from `but agentlog`.\"\nauthor: GitButler Team\n---\n\n# GitButler Agentlog Skill\n\nUse `but agentlog` to recover prior agent work from captured sessions.\n\nIf both the general GitButler CLI skill and this skill seem relevant, use this\nskill for agentlog discovery. Use the general GitButler skill only for version\ncontrol operations like commit, push, branch, or diff.\n\n## Core Workflow\n\nStart with the low-noise handoff command when the user wants recovered context:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog handoff\nbut agentlog handoff branch <branch-name-or-ref>\nbut agentlog handoff review <review-id-or-pull-request-key>\nbut agentlog handoff change <change-id-or-key>\n```\n\nUse the primitive commands as a narrowing funnel when `handoff` is too thin:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions review <review-id-or-pull-request-key> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions change <change-id-or-key> --limit 5\n\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n```\n\nFor handoff analysis, prefer JSON output internally so fields like previews,\nobserved targets, tool inputs, and record text are available without guessing\nfrom human display:\n\n```sh\nbut --json agentlog handoff\nbut --json agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\nbut --json agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\nbut --json agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n```\n\n1. Start with `handoff` for a clean orientation.\n2. If more detail is needed, use `sessions` for the branch, review / pull request / merge request, or change.\n3. Choose \n[TRUNCATED]\nt`: freshness signal.\n- `record_count` and `turn_count`: size estimate before hydration.\n- `related_turn_keys`: direct target evidence.\n- `match_evidence`: why the session was returned.\n- `observed_targets`: branch, review/PR/MR, or change keys observed in related turns.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: quick intent/result scan.\n\nRelated sessions are sorted by latest activity.\n\n## Reading `timeline`\n\nUse `timeline` to answer what happened in a session at turn granularity.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned turns versus total turns.\n- `turn_key`: handle for `records`.\n- `turn_index`: order within the session.\n- `capture_kind`: backfill or incremental.\n- `record_count`: turn size before hydrating records.\n- `source_record_index_range`: provider/source indexes covered by the turn.\n- `observed_targets`: targets observed in the turn.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: compact orientation.\n- `tool_counts`: tool call/result counts and tool names.\n\nIncrease `--limit` only when the current window misses the related turn or setup.\n\n## Reading `records`\n\nUse `records` to answer what exactly happened inside one turn.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned records versus total records in the turn.\n- `turn_record_index`: order within the turn.\n- `source_record_index`: original provider/source index when available.\n- `timestamp`, `kind`, `role`, `text`: message/tool orientation.\n- `tool_name` and `tool_input`: tool details when present.\n- `source_record`: redacted stored provider envelope for low-level debugging.\n\n`records` is intentionally bounded. Increase `--limit` only for a specific turn\nafter `timeline` shows that more detail is needed.\n\n## Handoff Summary\n\nWhen summarizing recovered context, include:\n\n- target used for discovery\n- previews explaining intent and outcome\n- minimal record snippets for the next action\n\nDo not lead with raw session or turn identifiers. Mention them only when the\nuser asks for evidence handles or when handing off to another command/tool.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:07:36.039Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}